<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-CAMPO-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DAY ONE ON JOB ONE ROUGH ONE FOR CAMPO
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MAC ENGEL 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ You never forget your first bicycle ride, first
day of school or first kiss.
</P>
<P>
   In the first game under Dave Campo, the Cowboys fell off the
bike, got kicked out of school and smacked by the girl, leaving no
doubt that he would never forget his first game as a head coach.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a rough day,'' Campo said. ``I didn't think [a bad
game] would be the first one, but I might as well get it out of the
way.''
</P>
<P>
   In a day that began so innocently, everything that could go
wrong did as the fifth coach in the 41-year history of the Cowboys
endured countless dubious firsts. Philadelphia toyed with Dallas
and won, 41-14, Sunday at Texas Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Whether it was watching Eagles running back Duce Staley run for
201 yards, Troy Aikman leave the game with a mild concussion or
tackle Erik Williams get ejected, Campo could never have known just
how rough his first game would be.
</P>
<P>
   1:01 p.m. _ A little more than two hours before kickoff, Campo
walks out of the locker room and heads down the tunnel to the field
for pregame warmups.
</P>
<P>
   Was the 29-year career assistant a little nervous?
</P>
<P>
   ``Nervous,'' Campo said, ``and excited.''
</P>
<P>
   3:05 p.m. _ First coin toss. A smashing success. The Cowboys win
it and elect for the game's first possession.
</P>
<P>
   14:56 of the first quarter _ First of many dubious signs. Kicker
David Akers of the Eagles executes a perfect onside kick that
Dameane Douglas recovers.
</P>
<P>
   10:44 _ First panic. Although silent on the sidelines, Campo
can't like what he sees when quarterback Troy Aikman is sacked on
the Cowboys' first play. Aikman is sacked two more times in the
next five plays.
</P>
<P>
   10:12 _ First Campo-is-an-offensive-genius applause. On the next
play, Rocket Ismail gains 37 yards on an end-around.
</P>
<P>
   :08 _ First dumb penalty. On third-and-one from Dallas 27,
Eagles quarterback Donovan McNabb floats a pass to the end zone for
Charles Johnson where safety Izell Reese is called for pass
interference. The Eagles score on the next play for a 14-0
first-quarter lead.
</P>
<P>
   13:40 of the second quarter _ First wish that this was only a
preseason game. Jeremiah Trotter intercepts Aikman's pass and
returns it 27 yards for a touchdown and a 21-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
   13:40 _ First verbally enunciated displeasure from crowd. Later,
as the game progresses, Campo hears his first boos.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everybody here wanted it for Dave,'' Cowboys owner/general
manager Jerry Jones said. ``But, this is not on him.''
</P>
<P>
   12:40 _ First Aikman concussion. In a right of passage for
Cowboys coaches, Aikman suffers a mild concussion when he's sacked
for the fourth time in the first half. He doesn't return.
</P>
<P>
   ``He cannot take shots like this all season, or we're going to
send him into early retirement,'' Cowboys running back Emmitt Smith
said.
</P>
<P>
   5:05 _ First pass completion/quarterback controversy. Backup
quarterback Randall Cunningham hits tight end Jackie Harris with a
pass that gains no yards.
</P>
<P>
   2:53 _ First points. Kicker Tim Seder caps a four-play, 2-yard
drive with a 34-yard field goal, cutting the deficit to 24-3.
</P>
<P>
   First first half _ Eagles 24, Cowboys 6.
</P>
<P>
   In the second half, the firsts were less numerous. But, there
was a positive, with some more negatives.
</P>
<P>
   6:45 of the fourth quarter _ First touchdown. Joey Galloway
catches a 4-yard pass from Cunningham, and the deficit is cut to
41-14.
</P>
<P>
   2:45 _ First natural disaster. Galloway is carted off the field
with a sprained left knee.
</P>
<P>
   2:45 _ First Erik Williams ejection. Failing to land his Joe
Frazier impersonation on an Eagle, Williams is kicked out of the
game.
</P>
<P>
   First game?
</P>
<P>
   ``We got our butts kicked, and now it's time to move on,'' Smith
said. ``We scored a touchdown and our field-goal kicker made two
field goals. That's the only positives.''
</P>
<P>
   And another.
</P>
<P>
   ``The great thing about it is that's [game] No. 1,'' Campo said.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, that might be a negative. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
