<HEADLINE>
NO SECOND-GUESSING ON GALLOWAY PLAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JEFF CAPLAN 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Cowboys coach Dave Campo said he won't
second-guess himself about playing wide receiver Joey Galloway late
in the fourth quarter of a rout. Galloway sprained his left knee
with less than three minutes remaining in the game.
</P>
<P>
   The severity of the injury was not initially known. Galloway,
who was on crutches after the game, was X-rayed, but results were
inconclusive. He will undergo an MRI test this morning.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're concerned anytime you have injuries like that,'' Cowboys
owner and general manager Jerry Jones said. ``We are concerned
about Joey's injury.''
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys traded two first-round draft picks to Seattle for
Galloway, who signed a $42 million contract during the off-season.
The speedy wideout was supposed to complement Raghib ``Rocket''
Ismail and replace the retired Michael Irvin.
</P>
<P>
   Galloway was not a factor until late in the game. He had one
catch for 22 yards in the first half. He finished with four catches
for 62 yards.
</P>
<P>
   If Galloway misses any games, James McKnight will likely be his
replacement. Wane McGarity is another possibility. McKnight and
McGarity each had one reception Sunday.
OFFICIALS EJECT WILLIAMS Right tackle Erik Williams had a game to
forget Sunday. The offensive line allowed five sacks and was
ineffective all day. The aggravation boiled over in the final
minutes of the game when Williams was ejected for throwing a punch
at an Eagles player.
</P>
<P>
   Williams, who held out for 28 days during training camp, had no
comment.
SEDER SUCCESSFUL Kicker Tim Seder proved to be the lone offensive
highlight for the Cowboys. The former school teacher made both of
his field-goal attempts, from 34 and 38 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Sunday was the first time Seder kicked in a real game since Nov.
22, 1997, when he played for Ashland University against Slippery
Rock in the NCAA Division II playoffs. He missed his only attempt
that day from 42 yards. The last time Seder was successful on a
field-goal attempt came against the University of Indianapolis on
Nov. 8, 1997.
AIKMAN, SMITH STALLED Quarterback Troy Aikman made no progress in
moving into the NFL's top 20 for career passing yards. He remained
21st in league history with 31,310 career passing yards, 238 yards
behind John Brodie (31,548). His five pass attempts puts him 18 shy
of moving past Ken Anderson into 20th on the NFL's career pass
attempts list.
</P>
<P>
   Emmitt Smith's 29 rushing yards left him 8 yards shy of becoming
the third player in NFL history to rush for 14,000 yards in a
career. He will join Walter Payton and Barry Sanders.
BRIEFLY The 109-degree temperature at game time set a Cowboys
record, home or away. They played in 101-degree heat on Sept. 7,
1997 at Arizona. The Texas Stadium record was 99 degrees against
the Cardinals on Sept. 20, 1992.
</P>
<P>
   Jason Tucker's two-game streak of consecutive 100-yard receiving
games was stopped. Tucker closed the 1999 regular season with
back-to-back 100-yard games. Sunday, he did not line up at wide
receiver.
</P>
<P>
   Cornerback Kareem Larrimore became the first rookie to start a
season opener at cornerback for the Cowboys since Ron Francis
opened the 1987 season at St. Louis.
</P>
<P>
   Middle linebacker Dat Nguyen was taken to the lockerroom at the
8:03 mark of the third quarter and was treated for dehydration.
</P>
<P>
   On the sideline: G Al Jackson, CB Dwayne Goodrich (left
hamstring), DT Michael Myers, CB Charlie Williams (left knee), CB
Mario Edwards (left hamstring), LB Orantes Grant, G Kelvin Garmon,
WR Chris Brazzell.
INJURY REPORT
</P>
<P>
   Quarterback Troy Aikman (mild concussion) _ CT scan, negative.
Will be reevaluated today.
</P>
<P>
   Receiver Joey Galloway (sprained left knee) _ magnetic resonance
imaging exam today.
</P>
<P>
   Quarterback Randall Cunningham (sprained right thumb) _
reevaluated today. nn
</P>
