<HEADLINE>
GRASS FIELD TAKES A BEATING; FINES FOR HILLIARD AND DIXON; GARNES
KNOCKED OUT; LONGEST RUN IN 41 YEARS; ANOTHER STORMY DAY 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. _ The new grass at Giants Stadium had a
shaky NFL debut. After the portion down the middle of the field was
replaced last week, heavy showers Saturday apparently loosened some
of the sod. Two gaping pieces came out after a pileup caused by a
fumble by Arizona quarterback Jake Plummer late in the first half.
One resembled a New York City pothole.
</P>
<P>
   Officials spent some of their time patching the holes, and the
grounds crew tried halftime maintenance. A Giants Stadium worker
was tending to the field after fans left.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was coming up,'' Giants offensive lineman Lomas Brown said.
``When they were fighting for that fumble, there were a lot of
divots.''
</P>
<P>
   Tiki Barber had no complaints. He said he loved running on grass
after accumulating 144 yards on 13 carries. Barber tore a knee
ligament on the old artificial turf here in 1997.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Fines For Hilliard And Dixon
</P>
<P>
   Wide receivers Ike Hilliard, a veteran starter, and Ron Dixon, a
rookie, missed practice Saturday and will be fined the team
maximum. Coach Jim Fassel said the players were staying together
and overslept until a team telephone call awoke them. Fassel
considered suspending them for the game but did not think that
would have been fair to their teammates, and he thought that not
starting but playing them would be ceremonial. Fassel discussed his
decision with the team captains before announcing the fines. He did
not disclose the amount of the fines.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not taking it lightly,'' Fassel said. ``I'm not happy with
it. They know it.''
</P>
<P>
   Teams walk through their plays on Saturdays as a final tuneup
for the game.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Garnes Knocked Out
</P>
<P>
   Safety Sam Garnes sustained a concussion in a fourth-quarter
collision with Jessie Armstead and was taken to the Hospital for
Special Surgery in New York City for tests.
</P>
<P>
   Armstead's right shoulder hit the left side of Garnes' helmet,
and the safety lay face down and motionless on the field for over a
minute. Fassel said Garnes lost consciousness for 30 to 40 seconds
and was still foggy afterward. He walked to a cart that drove him
off the field.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Longest Run In 41 Years &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Tiki Barber's 78-yard touchdown run was the longest for the
Giants since Frank Gifford ran 79 yards against Washington in 1959.
Hap Moran's 91-yard run against Green Bay in 1930 is the longest in
team history. Eddie Price ran 80 yards at Philadelphia in 1951. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Another Stormy Day
</P>
<P>
   The only other lightning delay in Giants Stadium football
history occurred in a Jets-Colts game in 1996. Kansas City played
host to Seattle and the league's last lightning delay in 1998. ...
The Giants are 4-0 on opening day under Fassel. They have lost the
next two games in each of his previous three years.
</P>
</TEXT>
