authors with a spiritual bent like Neale Donald Walsch, the author
of ``Conversations With God,'' who in June took readers on an
eight-day tour of Peru timed to coincide with the summer solstice
sunrise over Machu Picchu. But there are also published historians
and even a poet who are leading people on tours ripped from their
chapters, whether it be a stroll down Shankill Road in Belfast or a
trip to Colonial Williamsburg in Virginia. By Doreen Carvajal.
</P>
