<P>
   FOR HORMONE REPLACEMENT THERAPY, ONE HIGH-DOSE SIZE MAY NOT FIT
ALL
</P>
<P>
   HEALTH-HORMONE-REPLACEMENT-LIFEBEAT _ Nowadays, it seems as if
only people with a Ph.D. in epidemiology _ and preferably circus
experience _ can juggle all the pros and cons of hormone
replacement therapy, much less make sense of all the conflicting
reports. As if the choices the treatment itself poses weren't
complicated enough, now medical researchers are challenging the
popular notion that the same-size dose fits all women. That means
the million-dollar question facing women of menopausal age _ do I
or don't I? _ may soon be eclipsed by an even trickier one: How
much is right for me? By Kathleen McAuliffe. 1,350 words.
</P>
<P>
   HALLIE KATE EISENBERG: PRINCESS OF POP
</P>
<P>
   PEPSI-GIRL-LIFEBEAT _ At age 8, Hallie Kate Eisenberg has a
career that would make most actresses jealous: She worked with Al
Pacino and Russell Crowe in last year's Oscar-nominated ``The
Insider'' and plays Minnie Driver's daughter in ``Beautiful.'' Then
there are the Pepsi ads that catapulted her to fame, in which she
channels the voices of such legends as Aretha Franklin and Marlon
Brando. Not bad for someone too young to stay up for her six guest
spots on ``The Tonight Show.'' By Jessica Brown. 650 words.
</P>
