 &HT;    Increase your cultural awareness
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.afroam.org/children/children.html _ Learn more about Africa
and African American heritage on this artfully designed site geared
for kids. Test your knowledge of African animals, take a black
history quiz and discover the diverse cultures found in Africa.
There are also a dozen games, not necessarily with cultural
content, that require Shockwave, a downloadable animation program.
Perhaps the smartest feature on the site is a series of illustrated
myths and fables from around the world, including ``The Lion and
the Hare,'' from Ethiopia and ``The Tiger, the Brahman and the
Jackal'' from India. The site is a sub part of the AFRO-Americ(at)
Web portal.
</P>
<P>
   www.kidcomics.com/en/index.htm _ For the smart-aleck kid, or
aspiring smart-alecks, this site is a must bookmark. Sure, it's got
some funny comics, but be sure to check out the practical guides:
``How to annoy your neighbors,'' ``How to get rid of a stupid
present'' and ``How to play phone pranks'' _ full of harmless,
creative ideas. Also worth a look are the ``cyberbooks,'' or mini
comic books you can read on your computer screen. You can also join
a subscriber list to receive updates on the site.
</P>
<P>
   _ Robert W. Gee
</P>
