<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Cartoon Network has to know geography to broadcast shows to 145
countries.
 &HT;    By Keith Still
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ If you like cartoons, you're not alone. Kids all over
the world are watching Bugs Bunny classics and newer shows such as
``Dexter's Laboratory'' on the 'toon-only channel Cartoon Network.
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta-based cable network is beamed into more than 118
million homes in 145 countries around the globe.
</P>
<P>
   Cartoon Network first aired in the United States on Oct. 1,
1992. Since then, it has expanded its library to include old
favorites, contemporary cartoons and network-created animated
shows.
</P>
<P>
   Today, 'toons on Cartoon Network are heard in 14 languages and
dialects, including Danish, Spanish, Portuguese, Dutch, French,
Italian, Polish, Swedish, Mandarin, Thai, Hindi, Japanese and
Tamil.
</P>
<P>
   Play our geography game by answering the following questions.
You may need to refer to a globe, encyclopedia or computer for
help. Don't forget our super-tough bonus question.
</P>
<P>
   When you're done, submit your answers to News for Kids at NFK
Cartoon Contest, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Include your
name, age, school, grade, phone number and address. Three lucky
winners will take home a prize package featuring your fave cartoon
characters, courtesy of Cartoon Network. You must be a
seventh-grader or younger to enter. Entries are due Sept. 11.
</P>
<P>
   1) Cartoon Network dubs its cartoons into different Spanish
dialects. ``Cow and Chicken'' rules the roost using the Castilian
dialect in this country.
</P>
<P>
   2) Most people in Latin American countries speak Spanish. But
the 'toon viewers in this large South American nation get their
Cartoon Network broadcasts in Portuguese. Name this country.
</P>
<P>
   3) This nation, located at about 14 degrees north latitude and
121 degrees east longitude, receives Cartoon Network's Asia-Pacific
broadcast.
</P>
<P>
   4) The Dragonball Z cartoon comes from the Land of the Rising
Sun, but it is tops among viewers in a country that once claimed
the sun never set on its empire. Name both countries.
</P>
<P>
   5) This country receives its broadcast on Cartoon Network's
European feed, but it's not a European nation. Go to approximately
1 degree south latitude, 36 degrees east longitude to find the
country's name.
</P>
<P>
   6) Down under, on this continent, ``The Flintstones'' rock.
</P>
<P>
   7) Tamil is spoken mainly in Sri Lanka and the southern part of
this subcontinent. Look north of Sri Lanka to find this neighbor.
</P>
<P>
   8) This North American nation receives its own special Cartoon
Network feed in Spanish from the network's headquarters in Atlanta.
</P>
