<P>
   Get your money's worth at these courses
</P>
<P>
   Avid NFL fans plugged into the Net
</P>
<P>
   Rams' linebacker: Just call me dot.com
</P>
<P>
   SAVE TIME ONLINE: All stories and urls on this page are one
click away on ajc.com/enews
</P>
<P>
   GEORGIA GOLF: Three Georgia courses make Maximum Golf's list of
the ``100 best value courses'' in the United States. The Brasstown
Valley Resort Golf Club in Young Harris, the Cherokee Run Golf Club
in Conyers and the Jekyll Island Golf Club (Oleander Course) all
offer ``your money's worth,'' according to the site. All 100
courses ``provide superb play, ice-cold beer, friendly folks,
outstanding vistas and prices that won't make you wince.''
</P>
<P>
   www.foxsports.com/maximumgolf/top100/
</P>
<P>
   SAVVY FANS: People who like professional football also like
computers, according to a survey by Scarborough Sports Marketing.
Sixty-three percent of avid NFL fans own a home computer and almost
25 percent of them use the Internet to keep up with sports scores.
</P>
<P>
   DOT.COM DEFENDER: St. Louis Rams linebacker London Fletcher is
an avid Web surfer. He even has a new nickname -- ``Dot.com'' _ and
will launch a new site this week. Check it out now and sign up for
an e-mail to let you know when it's up and running.
</P>
<P>
   www.dotcom59.com
</P>
