<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS05-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    By Rick Cantu
 &HT;    American-Statesman Staff
 &HT;    
 &HT;    The $42 million man lasted one game.
 &HT;    Joey Galloway was supposed to ignite a sagging offense, but the
new wide receiver for the Dallas Cowboys suffered a season-ending
knee injury in By BY Cowboys regrouping in wake of Philadelphia
massacre
 &HT;    By Rick Cantu
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ The $42 million man lasted one game.
</P>
<P>
   Joey Galloway was supposed to ignite a sagging offense, but the
new wide receiver for the Dallas Cowboys suffered a season-ending
knee injury in Sunday's 41-14 loss to Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
   Concern over the team's battered ego shifted to Galloway's torn
anterior cruciate ligament in his left knee on Monday. He was
carted off the field late in the fourth quarter after planting the
foot in the AstroTurf during a downfield block.
</P>
<P>
   ``He didn't have any serious tears,'' team owner Jerry Jones
said. ``He had a little bruising with the bone. He's obviously down
and very distressed about it. He basically told the doctor and me
there's no issue, as far as him rehabbing and coming back next
year.''
</P>
<P>
   In another matter, quarterback Troy Aikman suffered a ``mild''
concussion, and is listed as ``day-to-day'' for Sunday's game in
Arizona, Jones said. Aikman was dizzy and had headaches at a Dallas
hospital Sunday night, and he likely will not play Sunday against
Arizona if those symptoms continue today.
</P>
<P>
   The concussion was not as serious as the one he had in last
year's game in Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman, sacked only 19 times last year, was sacked four times in
the first half against Philadelphia. His day was over when Eagle
lineman Hugh Douglas dragged him to the turf with seven minutes
left in the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
   It marked the second time in Aikman's 12-year career that he
failed to complete a pass in a game. It was his ninth concussion.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys replaced Galloway by activating Arkansas rookie
quarterback Clint Stoerner off the practice squad Monday. He will
be the No. 2 quarterback _ behind Randall Cunningham _ if Aikman
does not play in Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   Cunningham, by the way, has a sprained right thumb and is
``questionable'' for the Cardinals game.
</P>
<P>
   As for Galloway, a major piece of the revamped offense leaves a
major void. He signed a seven-year, $42 million contract this year
and immediately was designated Aikman's chief receiver.
</P>
<P>
   Without him, Wane McGarity or James McKnight will be moved to
the starting lineup.
</P>
<P>
   Galloway's departure means Rocket Ismail is elevated to No. 1
receiver. He caught a career-high 80 passes last year, most of them
after longtime receiver Michael Irvin suffered a season-ending neck
injury in early October.
</P>
<P>
   Dave Campo admitted being ``embarrassed'' about his head
coaching debut. The hardest part of the week will be getting the
players to forget the Philadelphia massacre.
</P>
<P>
   ``The best way to do it is by finding out what we did wrong,
correct the mistakes, and go about our business,'' Campo said.
``We've got some good football players on this team and I expect
them to bounce back, period.''
</P>
<P>
   Campo said offensive tackle Erik Williams will be fined an
undisclosed amount by the team for being thrown out of Sunday's
game. He was ejected after a flagrant penalty late in the fourth
period.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
