allegations its tires caused dozens of traffic deaths, reached a
tentative agreement with steelworkers early today to avert a strike
at nine plants. The union has not yet disclosed details but said it
believed the agreement was fair for both sides. The settlement
covers more than 8,000 workers at seven plants that produce tires
and two that produce tire parts. By Steven Greenhouse.
