confirmed a Japanese report that it wants to amend the terms of its
proposed acquisition of a third of Mitsubishi Motors to obtain
greater control over the company, Japan's No. 3 automaker, which
has been buffeted by a recall scandal. DaimlerChrysler wants to
raise its Mitsubishi stake to 40 percent, altering its July plan to
buy 34 percent for almost $2 billion. It also wants more than the
current three seats on the 10-member management board.
DaimlerChrysler aims to wrest control of Mitsubishi Motors from
Mitsubishi group companies, which owned about 42 percent in March.
By Edmund L. Andrews.
