<P>
   BRITAIN-U.S.-ENERGY (Undated) _ On reports that National Grid
Group plc, which operates Britain's power transmission network, is
in talks to buy the U.S. firm Niagara Mohawk for about $3 billion.
The London-based National Grid has earmarked more for further
United States expansion this year, after buying New England
Electric System in March. Niagara, which has been reporting losses,
is seen as too small to compete in the deregulating American
market. By Andre Ross Sorkin.
</P>
