banks, including Credit Suisse Group, for accepting some of the
$670 million in deposits linked to the late Nigerian dictator Sani
Abacha. However, it imposed no penalties; they are not allowed
under current Swiss law. The Nigerian government is trying to
recover an estimated $3 billion in suspected embezzled state funds
sent abroad during General Abacha's 1993-98 rule.
</P>
