<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EUROPE-BOURSES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW INTEREST REPORTED IN LONDON STOCK EXCHANGE 
</HEADLINE>
   By SUZANNE KAPNER   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON _ Euronext, a company to be formed by merging the Paris,
Brussels and Amsterdam bourses, has held exploratory talks with two
French banks about raising money to bid for the London Stock
Exchange, people close to the discussions said.
</P>
<P>
   Euronext approached BNP Paribas and Societe Generale after last
week's hostile bid for the London Stock Exchange by OM Gruppen AB,
the Swedish company that runs the Stockholm exchange. OM's surprise
offer postponed a shareholder vote that was to decide the fate of
London's planned merger with Deutsche Borse of Germany and the
Nasdaq stock market of the United States to form a Pan-European
exchange called iX.
</P>
<P>
   The people familiar with Euronext cautioned that an outright bid
for the London Stock Exchange was not imminent, as the company must
first vote on its own merger on Sept. 22.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have increased the number of banks we are talking to, to
consider the present situation with the London Stock Exchange,''
said a person close to Euronext, who refused to be identified
further.
</P>
<P>
   Another person described the discussions as a ``chess move'' _
just one in a series of steps that Euronext is taking until it
unveils its full strategy sometime after the shareholder vote. The
Paris bourse will own 60 percent of Euronext, the Amsterdam
exchange will own 32 percent, and Brussels will hold 8 percent with
plans to offer the shares later this year.
</P>
<P>
   A representative of the Paris bourse declined to comment on the
situation, as did a spokesman for the London Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   Euronext approached the London Stock Exchange about an alliance
last May, but was rebuffed. The details of those discussions were
never disclosed to shareholders. Euronext has repeatedly stated its
interest in linking up with the London Stock Exchange.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
