the U.S. Open crowd after winning her match against Dokic. (Vincent
Laforet/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) PITTSBURGH -- Sept. 4, 2000 -- GORE-2 -- Democratic
presidential nominee Al Gore, who has been endorsed by most of the
nation's major unions, marching with the Rev. Jesse Jackson and
Democratic supporters in a Labor Day rally in Pittsburgh, Monday.
While in Pittsburgh, the vice president then noted a number of
achievements since he and President Bill Clinton took office in
1993, including replacing record federal deficits with record
federal surpluses and building ``the strongest economy in
history.'' (Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
